quran[40]{c,v,t}:
  19,59,"Then, there succeeded them generations who neglected and wasted the Prayer and followed (their) lusts, (abandoning the service of God’s cause). They will meet perdition (as their just deserts)"
  19,60,"Except those who repent and come to belief and do good, righteous deeds. Such will enter Paradise and will not be wronged in anything"
  19,61,Gardens of perpetual bliss which the All-Merciful has promised to His servants while unseen (beyond the perception and knowledge of the servants). His promise is ever sure of fulfillment
  19,62,"They will hear therein no idle talk, but only peace (contentment and safety). And they will have their provision therein morning and evening"
  19,63,"That is the Paradise which We will cause those of Our servants who are God-revering, pious to inherit (as theirs forever)"
  19,64,"(In response to an interval in the coming of Revelation, Gabriel explained:) We do not descend but by your Lord’s command only. To Him belongs whatever is before us and whatever is behind us and whatever is between (all time and space and whatever we do at all times in all places). And your Lord is never forgetful (so do not fear that He forgets you)"
  19,65,"(He is) the Lord of the heavens and the earth and all that is between them; so worship Him alone, and be constant and patient in His worship. Do you know of any whose name is worthy to be mentioned along with His (as Deity and Lord to worship)"
  19,66,"And (despite this, that disbelieving) human says: \"What? Once I am dead, will I then be brought forth alive"
  19,67,Does (that) human not bear in mind that We created him before when he was nothing
  19,68,"And so, by your Lord, We will most certainly raise to life and gather them all together, as well as the satans (of humankind and jinn whom they used to follow), before Us, and then We will most certainly heap them up on their knees in groups around Hell"
  19,69,Then We will certainly pluck out from every group of the same belief the ones who were most obstinate in rebellion against the All-Merciful
  19,70,"Indeed, We know best who deserves most (and before all others) to be thrown into Hell to roast therein"
  19,71,"There is no one among you, (O humankind,) who will not come to it. This is a fixed decree which your Lord has bound Himself to fulfill"
  19,72,"Then We will save those who keep from disobedience to Him in reverence for Him and piety, and We will leave in it the wrongdoers (who associate partners with God or deny Him), humbled on their knees"
  19,73,"When Our Revelations, clear as evidence and in meaning are recited (and conveyed) to them, those who persistently disbelieve say to those who believe: \"Which of the two parties (– you or us –) is superior in status with more impressive dwellings and more imposing as a company"
  19,74,"And yet, how many a generation have We destroyed before them who were superior in respect of possessions and outward show"
  19,75,"Say: \"Whoever is lost in error, no matter how much the All-Merciful adds (to their wealth and how long He prolongs their life-span), when they face what they were promised – whether it be punishment (here in this world) or the Last Hour – they will come to know who is worse in position and weaker in forces"
  19,76,"God strengthens in guidance those who have sought and found guidance. The righteous, good deeds of lasting merit are best in your Lord’s sight for reward, and best for returns"
  19,77,"Have you considered the one who disbelieves in Our Revelations and says (in insolence): \"(Whatever you say, I will continue just as I am, for) I will most certainly be given wealth and children"
  19,78,"Has he gained knowledge of the Unseen, or has he made a (particular, private) covenant with the All-Merciful"
  19,79,No indeed! But We will record what he says and saddle him (with its consequence) as an ever increasing punishment
  19,80,"And We will inherit of him what he says, and he will come to us quite alone (bereft of wealth and children)"
  19,81,They have taken deities apart from God so that they may be (a means of) might and glory for them
  19,82,"No indeed! Those (whom they deified – beings such as angels, jinn, Prophets, saints, and heroes, etc.) will deny their worship of them and turn against them as adversaries (on Judgment Day)"
  19,83,"Do you not see that We send the satans upon the unbelievers (because of their unbelief), and they impel them (towards sin and every kind of evil) with strong impulsion"
  19,84,"So be in no haste against them (so that their days and their persecutions of you might end sooner), for We but number for them a certain (fixed) number (of days, the time allotted for their respite)"
  19,85,"A Day (will come) when We will gather the God-revering, pious ones as honored guests of the All-Merciful (in Paradise)"
  19,86,And drive the disbelieving criminals to Hell like thirsty cattle
  19,87,"(Those who have taken deities so that they may intercede with God on their behalf should know that) none will have a right of intercession except such as have a covenant with the All-Merciful (by virtue of the quality of their faith and worship, and their nearness to Him)"
  19,88,"As it is, some say: \"The All-Merciful has taken to Himself a child"
  19,89,Assuredly you have (in such an assertion) brought forth something monstrous –
  19,90,"The heavens are all but rent, and the earth split asunder, and the mountains fall down in ruins –"
  19,91,That they ascribe to the All-Merciful a child
  19,92,It is not for the All-Merciful to take to Himself a child
  19,93,There is none in the heavens and the earth but comes to the All-Merciful as a servant
  19,94,"Most certainly He knows and registers them, and has numbered them exactly, (having appointed for every being a particular service or duty, and determined for each a life-span and provision)"
  19,95,"And every one of them will appear before Him on the Day of Resurrection, quite alone (bereft of all worldly things, children and family, friends and helpers)"
  19,96,"Assuredly, those who believe and do good, righteous deeds, the All-Merciful will assign for them love (in the hearts of the inhabitants of the heaven and many on the earth, so that they will receive welcome throughout creation, no matter if they are weak and small in number now)"
  19,97,"We make it (this Qur’an) in your tongue and easy (to recite and understand) so that you may thereby give glad tidings to the God-revering, pious ones, and warn thereby a people given to contention"
  19,98,"And how many a generation We have destroyed before them! Can you feel (the existence) of a single one of them, or hear any whisper of them"